prvtCESMib.name: prvtCESMib

revisions.description: Modified values for objects prvtCESModulePolicyLops, prvtCESModulePolicyRbit, prvtCESModulePolicyRd

Added new objects prvtCESClearPortStatistics, prvtCESModuleClearCircuitStatistics, prvtCESModuleLbit, prvtCESModulePolicyLops, prvtCESModulePolicyLbit, prvtCESModulePolicyRbit, prvtCESModulePolicyRd, prvtCESModulePolicyIdlePattern, prvtCESModulePolicyIdleSignalling
Added an additional port index to the alarm table.
Added the TCA alarms table objects and the TCA alarm trap.

prvtCESMib.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtCESMib.description: This module includes configuration parameters for DS1 modules not included in DS1-MIB.

ConfigAction.name: ConfigAction
ConfigAction.description: This value is used to specify what is to be done with unapplied CES module configuration.

E1Impedance.name: E1Impedance
E1Impedance.description: This value is used to configure E1 line type termination impedance.

T1LongCableLength.name: T1LongCableLength
T1LongCableLength.description: This value is used to configure T1 long cable length.

T1GainLimit.name: T1GainLimit
T1GainLimit.description: This value is used to configure T1 type Tx or Rx gain limit.

CESLineType.name: CESLineType
CESLineType.description: This value is used to configure the line mode common for all TDM ports of the module.

ServiceClock.name: ServiceClock
ServiceClock.description: This values are used to configure transmit clock as one of this modes.

prvtCESDsx1ExtTable.name: prvtCESDsx1ExtTable
prvtCESDsx1ExtTable.description: This table contains object for configuring DS1 interfaces, not supported in dsx1ConfigTable.

prvtCESE1Impedance.name: prvtCESE1Impedance
prvtCESE1Impedance.description: This object configures temination impedance for TDM ports if the line type is E1.

prvtCEST1GainLimit.name: prvtCEST1GainLimit
prvtCEST1GainLimit.description: This object configures Tx or Rx gain limit for TDM ports if the line type is T1.

prvtCESPortLineType.name: prvtCESPortLineType
prvtCESPortLineType.description: Additional line types. For reference see object dsx1LineType

prvtCEST1LongCableLength.name: prvtCEST1LongCableLength
prvtCEST1LongCableLength.description: Long cable length options for T1 mode.

prvtCESServiceClock.name: prvtCESServiceClock
prvtCESServiceClock.description: Service Clock available only for DS1 interface.

prvtCESUnappTable.name: prvtCESUnappTable
prvtCESUnappTable.description: This table displays CES module configuration which will take effect after prvtCESModuleConf is set to applyConfiguration(2).

prvtCESUnappLineType.name: prvtCESUnappLineType
prvtCESUnappLineType.description: The value of dsx1LineType before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappLineCoding.name: prvtCESUnappLineCoding
prvtCESUnappLineCoding.description: The value of dsx1LineCoding before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappLoopbackConfig.name: prvtCESUnappLoopbackConfig
prvtCESUnappLoopbackConfig.description: The value of dsx1LoopbackConfig before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappSignalMode.name: prvtCESUnappSignalMode
prvtCESUnappSignalMode.description: The value of dsx1SignalMode before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappTransmitClockSource.name: prvtCESUnappTransmitClockSource
prvtCESUnappTransmitClockSource.description: The value of dsx1TransmitClockSource before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappTransmitClockBackup.name: prvtCESUnappTransmitClockBackup
prvtCESUnappTransmitClockBackup.description: The value of dsx1TransmitClockBackup before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappLineLength.name: prvtCESUnappLineLength
prvtCESUnappLineLength.description: The value of dsx1LineLength before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappLineMode.name: prvtCESUnappLineMode
prvtCESUnappLineMode.description: The value of dsx1LineMode before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappLineBuildOut.name: prvtCESUnappLineBuildOut
prvtCESUnappLineBuildOut.description: The value of dsx1LineBuildOut before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappE1Impedance.name: prvtCESUnappE1Impedance
prvtCESUnappE1Impedance.description: The value of prvtCESE1Impedance before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappT1GainLimit.name: prvtCESUnappT1GainLimit
prvtCESUnappT1GainLimit.description: The value of prvtCEST1GainLimit before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappIPAddress.name: prvtCESUnappIPAddress
prvtCESUnappIPAddress.description: The CES Module IP address before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappIPAddressMask.name: prvtCESUnappIPAddressMask
prvtCESUnappIPAddressMask.description: The CES Module IP address mask before configuration is applied.

prvtCESUnappGateway.name: prvtCESUnappGateway
prvtCESUnappGateway.description: The CES Module Gateway before configuration is applied.

prvtCESModuleConfTable.name: prvtCESModuleConfTable
prvtCESModuleConfTable.description: This table contains object for configuring options that are applied to the entire module.

prvtCESModuleIndex.name: prvtCESModuleIndex
prvtCESModuleIndex.description: Index of each CES module installed.

prvtCESModuleTxClock.name: prvtCESModuleTxClock
prvtCESModuleTxClock.description: Configures Transmit Source Clock for the module.

prvtCESModuleTxBackupClock.name: prvtCESModuleTxBackupClock
prvtCESModuleTxBackupClock.description: Configures Backup Clock for the module.

prvtCESModuleConfig.name: prvtCESModuleConfig
prvtCESModuleConfig.description: When this object is set to applyConfiguration(2), the module is restarted and the changes in dsx1ConfigTable or prvtCESConfTable are applied. The object must be set to rejectConfiguration(3) to remove unapplied changes. If the object is set to restart(4), the module is restarted with applying the changes. This object always returns a value of noop(1) when get.

prvtCESModuleIPAddress.name: prvtCESModuleIPAddress
prvtCESModuleIPAddress.description: The CES Module IP address after configuration is applied.

prvtCESModuleIPAddressMask.name: prvtCESModuleIPAddressMask
prvtCESModuleIPAddressMask.description: The CES Module IP address mask after configuration is applied.

prvtCESModuleGateway.name: prvtCESModuleGateway
prvtCESModuleGateway.description: CES Module Gateway after configuration is applied.

prvtCESModuleLbit.name: prvtCESModuleLbit
prvtCESModuleLbit.description: Enable/disable L bit set upon AIS defect detection, in structure agnostic mode.

prvtCESModulePolicyLops.name: prvtCESModulePolicyLops
prvtCESModulePolicyLops.description: Controls policy lops. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyLbit.name: prvtCESModulePolicyLbit
prvtCESModulePolicyLbit.description: Controls policy lbit. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyRbit.name: prvtCESModulePolicyRbit
prvtCESModulePolicyRbit.description: Controls policy rbit. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyRd.name: prvtCESModulePolicyRd
prvtCESModulePolicyRd.description: Controls policy rd. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyIdlePattern.name: prvtCESModulePolicyIdlePattern
prvtCESModulePolicyIdlePattern.description: Controls policy idle pattern. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyIdleSignalling.name: prvtCESModulePolicyIdleSignalling
prvtCESModulePolicyIdleSignalling.description: Controls policy idle signalling. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyLopsEnter.name: prvtCESModulePolicyLopsEnter
prvtCESModulePolicyLopsEnter.description: Controls the number of consecutive missed packets required to enter LOPS state. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyLopsExit.name: prvtCESModulePolicyLopsExit
prvtCESModulePolicyLopsExit.description: Controls the number of consecutive missed packets required to exit LOPS state. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrLbit.name: prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrLbit
prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrLbit.description: If a packet is received with L bit set, and the payload is present (not suppressed), one of the following is sent to the TDM line, according to a globally configurable unstructured L-flag policy: The AIS pattern all-one The received payload as-is none

prvtCESModulePolicyuStrReplace.name: prvtCESModulePolicyuStrReplace
prvtCESModulePolicyuStrReplace.description: If a missing packet is detected, one of the following is sent to the TDM line, according to a globally configurable structured missing packet replacement policy: The AIS pattern all-one on the relevant timeslots The configured IDLE pattern

prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrReplace.name: prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrReplace
prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrReplace.description: If a missing packet is detected, one of the following is sent to the TDM line, according to a globally configurable unstructured missing packet replacement policy: The AIS pattern all-one The configured IDLE pattern

prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrLops.name: prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrLops
prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrLops.description: If a CES circuit enters the LOPS state, one of the following is sent to the TDM line, according to a globally configurable unstructured missing packet replacement policy: The AIS pattern all-one The contents of the jitter buffer - none

prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrReplacePattern.name: prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrReplacePattern
prvtCESModulePolicyuUnstrReplacePattern.description: Unstructured packet replace policy pattern number

prvtCESDsx1AlarmTable.name: prvtCESDsx1AlarmTable
prvtCESDsx1AlarmTable.description: This table contains object for configuring and displaying TDM ports TCA thresholds.

prvtCESDsx1AlarmPort.name: prvtCESDsx1AlarmPort
prvtCESDsx1AlarmPort.description: The DS1 port for which this alarm is configured.

prvtCESDsx1AlarmIndex.name: prvtCESDsx1AlarmIndex
prvtCESDsx1AlarmIndex.description: An integer uniquely identifying an alarm entry.

prvtCESDsx1AlarmVariable.name: prvtCESDsx1AlarmVariable
prvtCESDsx1AlarmVariable.description: The OID of the variable whose value is being monitored. Depending on the time interval, the error condition and the ifIndex of the TDM interface, this points to an object from an entry in dsx1CurrentTable or dsx1TotalTable.

prvtCESDsx1AlarmThreshold.name: prvtCESDsx1AlarmThreshold
prvtCESDsx1AlarmThreshold.description: The alarm condition threshold for this alarm entry. The alarm is triggered if the value of the object pointed by prvtCESDsx1AlarmVariable remains above this threshold for more than 3 seconds.

prvtCESDsx1AlarmValue.name: prvtCESDsx1AlarmValue
prvtCESDsx1AlarmValue.description: The value of the object pointed to by prvtCESDsx1AlarmVariable, present for notification purposes.

prvtCESCICTable.name: prvtCESCICTable
prvtCESCICTable.description: This table contains objects for configuring Clock Input Controller.

prvtCESCICNumber.name: prvtCESCICNumber
prvtCESCICNumber.description: An integer uniquely identifying a Clock Input Controller.

prvtCESCICClockNumber.name: prvtCESCICClockNumber
prvtCESCICClockNumber.description: This variable indicates the index of the clock the clock input controller belongs to

prvtCESCICMode.name: prvtCESCICMode
prvtCESCICMode.description: The mode of the clock input controller. Not all clock input controllers support all modes. The clock input controller status is 'locked' only if the clock input controller is in 'normal' mode.

prvtCESCICTdmPort.name: prvtCESCICTdmPort
prvtCESCICTdmPort.description: If the clock input controller recovers a clock from a port , this variable indicates the TDM Port. Otherwise, it must be set to zero.

prvtCESCICCircuit.name: prvtCESCICCircuit
prvtCESCICCircuit.description: If the clock input controller recovers a clock from a circuit, this variable indicates the circuit ID. Otherwise, it must be set to zero.

prvtCESCICStatus.name: prvtCESCICStatus
prvtCESCICStatus.description: The status of the input reference.Reference is ok when the status is 'locked'. Otherwise, the status is 'notLocked'. Alternatively, if an error was detected at the input, the status indicates this error.

prvtCESCICState.name: prvtCESCICState
prvtCESCICState.description: The state is set to 'active' if the input controller was selected by the clock to drive the clock output. At least one input out of the clock-input-controllers attached to a clock must be in an 'active' state at any given time

prvtCESCICMappTable.name: prvtCESCICMappTable
prvtCESCICMappTable.description: This table contains clock configuration and status monitoring information.

prvtCESCICMappClockNumber.name: prvtCESCICMappClockNumber
prvtCESCICMappClockNumber.description: Index for the conceptual row identifying a clock within this mapping table

prvtCESCICMappCICNumber.name: prvtCESCICMappCICNumber
prvtCESCICMappCICNumber.description: Index for the conceptual row identifying a clock input within this mapping table

prvtCESCICMappState.name: prvtCESCICMappState
prvtCESCICMappState.description: The state is set to 'active' if the input controller was selected by the clock to drive the clock output. At least one input out of the clock-input-controllers attached to a clock must be in an 'active' state at any given time This value of this variable is equal to the prvtCESCICState variable in the CIC table

prvtCESApsTable.name: prvtCESApsTable
prvtCESApsTable.description: This table contains objects needed APS configuration

prvtCESApsModuleId.name: prvtCESApsModuleId
prvtCESApsModuleId.description: An integer uniquely identifying slot of the CES module installed

prvtSdBerThreshold.name: prvtSdBerThreshold
prvtSdBerThreshold.description: The Signal Degrade Bit Error Rate. The negated value of this number is used as the exponent of 10 for computing the threshold value for the Bit Error Rate (BER). For example, a value of 5 indicates a BER threshold of 10^-5.

prvtSfBerThreshold.name: prvtSfBerThreshold
prvtSfBerThreshold.description: The Signal Failure Bit Error Rate. The negated value of this number is used as the exponent of 10 for computing the threshold value for the Bit Error Rate (BER). For example, a value of 5 indicates a BER threshold of 10^-5.

prvtCESUpdateFirmwareTable.name: prvtCESUpdateFirmwareTable
prvtCESUpdateFirmwareTable.description: This table contains object needed in update firmware of CES module

prvtCESModuleId.name: prvtCESModuleId
prvtCESModuleId.description: An integer uniquely identifying slot of the CES module installed

prvtCESFirmwareImageName.name: prvtCESFirmwareImageName
prvtCESFirmwareImageName.description: Name of the firmware image file

prvtCESUpdateStatus.name: prvtCESUpdateStatus
prvtCESUpdateStatus.description: The status of the last update procedure, if any. This object will have a value of updateStatusUnknown(2) if no update process has been performed.

prvtCESDsx1Alarm.name: prvtCESDsx1Alarm
prvtCESDsx1Alarm.description: This notification is sent when the value of a TDM port error condition statistic has exceeded the configured threshold.

prvtCESDsx1Compliance.name: prvtCESDsx1Compliance
prvtCESDsx1Compliance.description: The compliance statement for management of TDM ports.

prvtCESDsx1ROGroup.name: prvtCESDsx1ROGroup
prvtCESDsx1ROGroup.description: The group of objects with MAX-ACCESS read-write supported with read-only access for the first release.
